10 (2) The department shall set which days of the week the designated stretches of river will be
11 commercial fishing, guiding, and outfitting-free, except that one day must be Saturday.
12 (3) The designated stretches of rivers must be of a length or float time to provide for an average
13 day of recreational use.
14 (4) The department shall adopt rules to implement the provisions of this section by May 15, 2026.
15
16 NEW SECTION. Section 2. Codification instruction. [Section 1] is intended to be codified as an
17 integral part of Title 87, chapter 3, part 1, and the provisions of Title 87, chapter 3, part 1, apply to [section 1].
